    <comment>NEW PACKAGE

Vermouth is a lightweight game and application launcher for
running Windows executables through Proton or Wine on KDE.
It works like Lutris, Heroic, Faugus or Bottles, but is KDE first
(written in Qt/QML and using Kirigami).

- Bump to version 1.3.1
- Upstream changes:
  * fix: Building and packaging
  * fix: Better packaging
  * Updated Readme, added single click activation when hinted
  * feat: umu-launcher support
  * feat: Make the setting of the Global Drawer pinnable
  * feat: Add the ability to pin the drawer
  * Enable HDR per screen
  * feat: HDR toggle</comment>
